fr.ign.cogit.geoxygene.appli.render.groups

Class RenderingGroup

  • Object
    • RenderingGroup
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExternalGraphicRenderingGroup, FillRenderingGroup, RasterRenderingGroup, StrokeRenderingGroup

    public abstract class RenderingGroup
extends Object
    A RenderingGroup is an internal class of the Geoxygene GL rendeing pipeline that generates the parameters needed to actually do the rendering of a GLDisplayable with a given styling description.
    The key mecanism of a RenderingGroup relies in 3 methods :
    Given a styling element and -if needed- a RenderingMethodDescriptor ...
    • create() : Initializes the Rendering group by flattening the styling element of this group and extracting the parameters descriptions.
    • #filter() : Retains only the parameters descriptions also described in the RenderingMethodDescriptor.
    • fill(GLDisplayable, NamedRenderingParametersMap) : Generates a NamedRenderingParametersMap for a GLDisplayable which contains all the parameters needed to render this displayable.
    E.g : a PolygonSymbolizer will contain two groups : one for the rendering of its stroke and one for the rendering of its fill.
    Author:

    • Method Detail

      • getRenderingParameters

        public NamedRenderingParametersMap getRenderingParameters(GLDisplayable d)
        Get the rendering parameters corresponding to this RenderingGroup for the given GLDisplayable
        This method run the following pipeline:
        • 1 : call to #create(GLDisplayable)
        • 2 : call to #filter(GLDisplayable)
        • 3 : call to #fill(GLDisplayable, Map)
        Parameters:
        d - the GLDisplayable for wich parameters must be created.
        Returns:
        a set of rendering parameters that can be used by a DisplayableRenderer.

      • create

        protected abstract Map<String,Object> create()
        Get the parameters needed by this RenderingGroup. These parameters are usually extracted from the GLDisplayable symbolizer but can be anything. RenderingGroup.
        Returns:
        the parameters descriptors for this RenderingGroup.

      • filter

        protected NamedRenderingParametersMap filter(Map<String,Object> p,
                                             RenderingMethodDescriptor m)
        Retain only the parameters that are described in the given RenderingMethodDescriptor and return the parameters value associated with the parameters descriptors of the method. If not method is provided, this function will create a new RenderingMethodParameterDescriptor for each of the given parameter.
        Parameters:
        p - : the displayable
        m - : the rendering method for this RenderingGroup.
        Returns:
        the input parameters p filtered by the method m and matched with their RenderingMethodParameterDescriptor. THe result is stored in a NamedRenderingParametersMap that allow accesses to parameters through their name or the the uniform name they reference.
